data.content:
Three things break in EF Core 10. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` construction won't compile. Replace it with a simple lambda:

```csharp
// .NET 10 — no expression trees needed
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

All that manual expression tree plumbing is eliminated — conditionals go directly in the lambda body.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — uniquified & full-path nested

Two changes here:

- **Duplicate property names across complex types** (`ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street`) now get a numeric suffix to disambiguate. A migration will rename one column.
- **Nested complex types** now use the full path: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`).

**Fix:** Pin existing column names explicitly so no migration renames occur:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
    {
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
    {
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// For nested complex types:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    {
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
        {
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

Then run `dotnet ef migrations add VerifyNoChanges` — it should be empty.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method on this interface gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (redacted SQL for safe logging). Your implementation won't compile until you add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Apply the same addition to every other method you implement on this interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
